summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeVegane.l.f. Cosmetics' pigment-packed Camo Liquid Blush gives cheeks a long-lasting, dewy flush that's flattering as e.l.f. This liquid blush is lightweight and effortlessly blends out to a soft finish while the rounded, grooved applicator applies the perfect amount of blush every time.
details: DetailsBenefitsLong-lasting liquid blush delivers a high-pigment pop of color to cheeksLightweight formula with a soft, dewy finishBlendable & buildable to create the look you wantEasy to use rounded, grooved applicatorGreat for dry, oily & combination skinPairs well with e.l.f.'s Liquid Blush Brush (sold separately)e.l.f. is double-certified cruelty-free by Leaping Bunny & PETAe.l.f. is proud to partner with Fair Trade USA & manufacture products in Fair Trade Certified facilities; look for the Fair Trade Certified seal on your e.l.f. productFormulated WithoutPhthalatesParabensNonylphenol ethoxylatesTriclosanTriclocarbanHydroquinoneItem 2617738How To UseDab 1-2 dots onto cheeks with the applicator and blend with the e.l.f. Liquid Blush Brush (sold separately).IngredientsCoral Crush: Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Hydrogenated Poly(C6-14 Olefin), Octyldodecanol, Trimethylolpropane Triisostearate, Illite, Boron Nitride, Hydrogenated Styrene/Methyl Styrene/Indene Copolymer, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, C9-12 Alkane, Alumina, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Phenyl Trimethicone, Ethylene/Propylene/Styrene Copolymer, Sorbitan Sesquioleate, Propylene Carbonate, Aluminum Hydroxide, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Ethylhexylglycerin, Tin Oxide, Butylene/Ethylene/Styrene Copolymer, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Tocopherol, Rosa Damascena Flower Water, Water (Aqua), Ricinus Communis (Castor) Seed Oil, Sodium Hyaluronate, Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Hibiscus Mutabilis Flower Extract, Phenoxyethanol. May Contain: Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Yellow 6 lake (CI 15985), Red 28 Lake (CI 45410), Red 6 Lake (CI 15850), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140), Red 7 Lake (CI 15850).Ingredients may change or vary from time to time. Please refer to the packaging of the product you receive for the list of ingredients in your particular product.
how_to_use: Dab 1-2 dots onto cheeks with the applicator and blend with the e.l.f. Liquid Blush Brush (sold separately).

reviews.headline: Would buy again!
reviews.comments: Dewy without being glossy. Very complimentary color and could be built up if you wanted. Blends very nicely.

reviews.headline: Great Buy!
reviews.comments: Beautiful color and pigmenation.

reviews.headline: Great Buy!
reviews.comments: Wonderful pigmentation and texture.

reviews.headline: Would buy again
reviews.comments: This product is really nice. The color pay off is good, but I did not wear it for more than 4 hours so I am not sure of how long this cream blush will last. I would buy this product in another color. Easy to use and blendable. [I received this product in exchange for my honest review]

reviews.headline: Love the lilac colod
reviews.comments: I received this product for free for my honest review and I thought the product worked really well. The lilac color was pigmented but was buildable. You can use a light wash of color and blend it out or build it up depending on how much you used .

reviews.headline: ALL I NEED
reviews.comments: These are IT.  They will last forever.  Gorgeous gorgeous.  No need for highlight!  Super pigmented - a little goes a long way so the best way to use these is to tap the product onto your hand, and use the ELF blush brush (a loosely packed angled brush).  Work blush into the brush and then lightly tap onto the cheekbones.  I'm super fair and I was able to used Bronze Bombshell!  I also have Peach Perfect and Dusty Rose.  I'll probably end up with all the colors eventually.

reviews.headline: Beautiful Prosuct but caused Breakouts
reviews.comments: This product has a beautiful application and rich pigmentation, but caused breakouts for me. I would not recommend for anyone with sensitive skin.

reviews.headline: A little goes a LONG way!
reviews.comments: This is the most pigmented blush I have ever used, and it came with a bit of a learning curve as a result. If you're applying this directly to you face, one tiny little dot is all you need, I promise. I use the shade Pinky Promise on true neutral, fair skin. The finish is gorgeous, it's lasts all day, and the color is the perfect neutral pink once applied to my face (though it says it's a cool tone). I don't see a way I ever run out of this product with how little I need to use.

reviews.headline: Sooo good
reviews.comments: One of the best drugstore blushes and on a budget too!! I have dusty rose and cannot wait to purchase more shades!!

reviews.headline: Not The Best
reviews.comments: It's honestly too pigmented, impossible to blend, and looks a bit splotchy and patchy on my skin. it reminds me of acrylic paint. feels really heavy and smears. Looks cakey too

reviews.headline: Love this product!
reviews.comments: I bought this because I needed a liquid blush that wasn't expensive. I expected the product to be ok but I used it and it is now my favorite liquid blush. The color is amazing and it gives you a sun-kissed glowy look. It is extremely easy to blend too. But just a warning it is pigmented. I love this product and will definitely be repurchasing.

reviews.headline: Okay blush
reviews.comments: This e.l.f. blush was okay. I don't normally use a liquid blush. It went on okay. I didn't care for the color. I would try a different color in the future. I received this product in exchange for my honest review.

reviews.headline: Blends nicely.
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I did enjoy this blush. I feel like it blended nicely. I would probably personally have picked a slightly different color, as I prefer light pinky shades. But I do still like and use it.

reviews.headline: I would buy this product again
reviews.comments: A good high quality product. That I liked and easy to blend and build. Also plenty of product so will last me a while

reviews.headline: Blush to last you a year!!
reviews.comments: Soo I've always been a powder blush girly until I found the e.l.f camo liquid blush and let me tell you even though the bottle is a bit small its good for the price and a little bit goes a long way. Just a small dab on my cheeks and nose gives a perfect glowy sun kissed look. And this bottle will last awhileeeee. Try it for yourself and see < 3

reviews.headline: Good product!!!
reviews.comments: I love this product and its a great deal. This lasted me so long and works so well. The only bad thing about it is its kinda hard to blend. But all and all i love this product.

reviews.headline: Love this color blush
reviews.comments: I am not usually a blush person, however, the color of this blush appealed to me And lo and behold I absolutely love this color blush. I probably will not wear any other Or color blushes, but this one won Me over. [I received this product in exchange for my honest review]

reviews.headline: Great for Cool undertones
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] i love this volor on cool undertone akin ! Its a beautiful lavender purpke color. Very pigmented

reviews.headline: Super Pigment!
reviews.comments: I have the lilac and the coral crush and I absolutely love them! I get so much coverage just from one dot on each cheek but I love blush so I do two. These last all day! The only thing is that they dry quickly so blend quickly.

reviews.headline: Pretty blush, messy packaging
reviews.comments: I recently swapped my Rare Beauty liquid blush for this Elf Dupe in a pinch. The pigment is great and only needs 1-2 dots on your cheeks. The coverage is great and the colors are beautiful and vibrant. However, the packaging is horrible. The blush is constantly seeping out of the sides of the cap when trying to close it and getting all over my makeup products and makeup bag.I have to clean the entire cap 2-3x a week and this is wasting sooo much product. At this point, I am about to just throw the blush away as it is getting all over the place. Again, love the color and product but we need new packaging.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I purchased this around the time it  launched.  I purchased the Comin' In Hot Pink and Coral Crush. 

The Hot Pink one is pigmented for sure.  That said I would suggest trying out on hand first.  Then either trying out fist by playing on back of hand first then dipping the Liquid blush brush I also have, but you can use yours of choice and or a moist sponge if you like. Personally I favor brushes. Both work well. These are fun and more fun..decent I quality and lasts pretty long especially after settling with a bit of powder if you wish. I feel these two shades would compliment most skin tones.  I'm not fair but a light neutral in winter. I recommend!
faceoff_positive.headline: Fun and pigmented in a good way.

faceoff_negative.comments: Thoughts on the blush: I'm wearing Suave Mauve for the first time today and am lowkey disappointed. The color looks beautiful in the swatch, but sheers out to a rather warmish pink on my fair cool complexion. I bought Bronze Bombshell hoping that it would be a cool 90s brown, but it's remarkably orange. Worst of all, I wore Suave Mauve today and my oily skin ate it for breakfast - it disappeared almost immediately. Thank u, next.
faceoff_negative.headline: Meh product
